data.title: I was born into an Irish Catholic family. I stopped going to church as soon as I was allowed not to. Then I developed a drug and alcohol...
data.meta_description:
9,952 likes, 592 comments - robbiewilliams on July 22, 2023: "I was born into an Irish Catholic family.

I stopped going to church as soon as I was allowed not to.
Then I developed a drug and alcohol problem.
And I was told I had a ‘’God-shaped hole. This made sense, as I guessed I’d been to hell.
And when I tried stopping, I got down on my knees and prayed to a god of my understanding.
My god then was similar, I guess, to the image of Archangel Michael, but not a religious god.
I felt heard.

As soon as I got back on my metaphorical feet. I stopped praying.
It seems I only pray in emergencies.

Then I saw some videos online, and I became an atheist.

Now I’m not an atheist.

Now I’m not anything.

But I LOVE Angels . badass, fire, and fury angels

So I guess I'm an angel-ist...

That is, after all, what the song is about.

But I also like shopping. I love shopping. Not all the time, but when I do, I fucking love it.

So, subject to change, Im a Materialistic angel-ist.".
